article.headline: Army 60, Columbia 57
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Matt Bell scored 20 points and made all 11 of his free throw attempts to lead Army over Columbia 60-57 Friday night in the season opener for both teams. Josh Wilson and Travis Owsley had nine points apiece for the Black Knights. Bell added four steals. Matt Land led the Lions with 15 points and was 7-of-9 from the free throw line, while Gerard Barrett had 13 points and was 7-of-10 from the free throw line. Barrett, Matt Preston, Dalen Cuff were all fouled out. Despite the loss, Columbia outrebounded Army 45-20.
